<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-521-875  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 521 875.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 31 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Double speed floppy drive due this month. (Y.E. Data)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Takahashi, Ken.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Y.E. Data (product development).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentFloppy DiskDisk DrivesPerformance Improvement.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>DOUBLE SPEED FLOPPY DRIVE DUE THIS MONTH TOKYO, JAPAN, 1990 AUG 31 (NB) --Y.E.andP;  Data has developed FDD (floppy disk drive) units which read and writedata and format a floppy disk in half the time it takes for an existing FDD.andM;In order to meet the higher processing speed of computers, hard disk andoptical disk drive units have been made faster while FDD units have simplybeen made lighter and larger, neglecting higher-speed.andP;  For this reason, Y.E.andO;Data has decided to develop FDD units which are twice as fast as conventionalfloppy drives, and has done so by doubling the rotating speed of a floppydisk.andM;The new FDD units will be available at the end of this month.andP;  Samples willbe 35,000 yen ($230) for the 3.5-inch unit and 40,000 yen ($270) for the5.25-inch unit.andP;  As current floppy disks can be used in the double speed FDDunits, Y.E.andP;  Data expects to see a wide variety of applications, and isaiming to sell 3,000 units each month.andM;(Ken Takahashi/19900830)</TEXT></DOC>